          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2021-03-23T13:48:24Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text>
            <![CDATA[ <p><b>No Coronavirus Copays for Veterans Act</b></p> <p>This bill prohibits the Department of Veterans Affairs from requiring a co-payment or other cost sharing for qualifying preventive services related to COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019). A qualifying preventive service is intended to prevent or mitigate COVID-19 and is either (1) an evidence-based item or service with an <i>A</i> or <i>B</i> rating in the current recommendations of the U.S. Preventive Services Task Force, or (2) an immunization that has in effect a recommendation from the Advisory Committee on Immunization Practices of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention with respect to the individual involved.</p> <p>Such a prohibition shall take effect 15 business days after the date on which a recommendation is made regarding a qualifying preventive service related to COVID-19.</p>]]>
          </text>
          <updateDate>2021-02-23T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
